Orchestrates the full cage execution lifecycle across three phases: `prepare` (validates preconditions, mints run directory, materializes cage rules, resolves runtime), `run` (stands up API proxy thread for billed modes, execs cage via bwrap, captures exit code and proxy diagnostics), and `teardown` (best-effort cleanup). Also loads `.cagevars` file at bin startup before argument parsing.

The `Resolved` struct carries all inputs needed for one run: target project root, task id, mode, paths to three injected binaries (`ctx-verify`, `ctx-context`, `ctx-scan`), and flags for dirty-tree and verbose logging. `execute(r)` guarantees teardown runs even if prepare or run fails, preventing stranded run directories.

Target root path must be canonicalized before bwrap invocation because bwrap binds it at the identical path inside the cage (ADR-046) alongside other absolute binds; a relative path causes bwrap to create those mount points as real directories on the host instead of inside the sandboxed root.

Teardown errors are swallowed; `RunOutcome` captures the caged process exit code plus an optional proxy diagnostic (best-effort, never overrides the exit code per ADR-027). `env` submodule holds bind/env resolution for `BwrapConfig`, split only to stay under file-length limits.